-- Hiscox Plans to Name Underwriter Childs as Chairman, Times Says
-- B y   J e s s e   W e s t b r o o k
-- 2012-04-22T10:31:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/hiscox-plans-to-name-underwriter-childs-as-chairman-times-says.html
Hiscox Ltd. (HSX) , a Lloyd’s of London
insurer, plans to name Robert Childs, its chief underwriter, as
chairman, the Sunday Times reported, without saying where it got
the information.  Bermuda-based Hiscox has notified the Bermuda Monetary
Authority and the U.K.’s Financial Services Authority of its
plans, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jesse Westbrook in London at 
 jwestbrook1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dick Schumacher at 
 dschumacher@bloomberg.net  